1
00:00:56,500 --> 00:01:00,900
When people finish their day
and hurry home,

2
00:01:01,375 --> 00:01:03,125
my day starts.

3
00:01:20,724 --> 00:01:25,402
My diner is open from midnight
to 7:00 in the morning.

4
00:01:25,402 --> 00:01:28,694
They call it "Midnight Diner."

5
00:01:34,292 --> 00:01:36,041
Do I even have customers?

6
00:01:36,297 --> 00:01:38,297
More than you would expect.

7
00:01:40,634 --> 00:01:42,621
MIDNIGHT DINER: TOKYO STORIES

8
00:01:42,621 --> 00:01:48,443
SWEET ROLLED OMELET

9
00:01:57,575 --> 00:02:00,950
Such a big eggplant could only
be called "jumbo eggplant."

10
00:02:01,260 --> 00:02:04,390
A friend of mine sent them after
quitting her job and returning home.

11
00:02:04,390 --> 00:02:05,719
How do you eat them?

12
00:02:05,945 --> 00:02:09,737
In Takayama, we grill them
with miso in the middle.

13
00:02:10,232 --> 00:02:13,107
Here. Fried fish with less rice.

14
00:02:13,842 --> 00:02:17,092
Master, if you've got a minute,
can you cook these?

15
00:02:17,495 --> 00:02:18,495
Sure.

16
00:02:27,700 --> 00:02:28,866
Welcome.

17
00:02:30,825 --> 00:02:31,542
Beer?

18
00:02:31,866 --> 00:02:32,783
Sure.

19
00:02:33,291 --> 00:02:34,182
Is this the right place?

20
00:02:34,182 --> 00:02:35,182
I think so.

21
00:02:36,566 --> 00:02:38,091
Have you seen this man here?

22
00:02:38,091 --> 00:02:39,966
Shall I help them?

23
00:02:42,259 --> 00:02:44,968
Have you seen this man here?

24
00:02:48,247 --> 00:02:48,928
Here you go.

25
00:02:50,134 --> 00:02:52,801
Have you seen this man here?

26
00:02:52,801 --> 00:02:53,634
Hey...

27
00:02:54,614 --> 00:02:55,697
Never mind. It's okay.

28
00:02:56,592 --> 00:02:58,128
I scan you, you scan me.

29
00:02:58,128 --> 00:03:00,078
Pay with e-money, okay?

30
00:03:00,926 --> 00:03:03,031
This is... This is...

31
00:03:03,031 --> 00:03:05,031
Cash only. Cash only.

32
00:03:09,450 --> 00:03:10,866
Sorry to have disturbed you. Goodbye.

33
00:03:12,700 --> 00:03:13,616
Hey...

34
00:03:18,536 --> 00:03:21,703
He said, "Sorry to have bothered you.
Keep the change."

35
00:03:22,091 --> 00:03:23,857
He said so. Maybe.

36
00:03:25,511 --> 00:03:28,951
Aren't they survivors of
the Hong Kong mafia,

37
00:03:28,951 --> 00:03:31,367
who once had a big fight
with the local yakuza?

38
00:03:32,114 --> 00:03:34,781
Could be. They looked like that.

39
00:03:37,991 --> 00:03:39,202
Dangerous smell.

40
00:03:41,315 --> 00:03:42,315
Certainly.

41
00:03:44,550 --> 00:03:47,650
Throw it by hand
by supporting with your waist.

42
00:03:53,063 --> 00:03:54,396
Anything wrong?

43
00:03:56,152 --> 00:03:57,652
What?

44
00:04:10,116 --> 00:04:11,701
Master class technique.

45
00:04:12,031 --> 00:04:13,031
Are you her master?

46
00:04:13,475 --> 00:04:14,850
Just a passerby.

47
00:04:15,464 --> 00:04:17,006
A passerby...

48
00:04:20,867 --> 00:04:22,035
Hello, Master.

49
00:04:23,451 --> 00:04:27,743
This person would like
to have a rolled omelet.

50
00:04:32,675 --> 00:04:33,390
Please.

51
00:04:36,044 --> 00:04:36,723
Sure.

52
00:04:55,235 --> 00:04:56,042
Here you go.

53
00:05:10,575 --> 00:05:12,482
Ours is a bit sweet.

54
00:05:20,066 --> 00:05:25,184
This tastes similar to the one
my dad used to make when I was little.

55
00:05:25,943 --> 00:05:28,963
His was sweeter than this.

56
00:05:30,271 --> 00:05:31,354
I see.

57
00:05:32,111 --> 00:05:34,951
I'll add more sugar next time.

58
00:05:44,035 --> 00:05:46,077
Thank you. Check please.

59
00:05:47,236 --> 00:05:48,570
It's 400 yen.

60
00:05:53,834 --> 00:05:55,418
You speak Japanese very well.

61
00:05:56,690 --> 00:05:58,773
I studied it before.

62
00:05:59,369 --> 00:06:01,078
It's none of my business...

63
00:06:01,695 --> 00:06:04,111
but people came here to look for you.

64
00:06:06,548 --> 00:06:08,006
I'm Lee.

65
00:06:10,114 --> 00:06:12,281
That was very delicious.

66
00:06:20,086 --> 00:06:23,267
Lee visited here again and again
after that day,

67
00:06:23,566 --> 00:06:26,025
and had a sweet rolled omelet.

68
00:06:36,023 --> 00:06:38,565
You do like rolled omelets.

69
00:06:39,551 --> 00:06:40,665
Do you like it?

70
00:06:42,039 --> 00:06:42,999
Yes, it's delicious.

71
00:06:44,594 --> 00:06:46,594
Where did you learn Chinese?

72
00:06:47,419 --> 00:06:49,910
Last year, I started teaching
Japanese as a volunteer

73
00:06:49,910 --> 00:06:52,489
and learning Chinese
from my students in exchange.

74
00:06:52,489 --> 00:06:55,406
I like watching their historical dramas.

75
00:06:56,897 --> 00:06:59,064
How about you? How do you know him?

76
00:06:59,713 --> 00:07:05,088
I've met him,
but I don't actually know him.

77
00:07:13,316 --> 00:07:14,233
Welcome.

78
00:07:14,788 --> 00:07:15,663
Hey.

79
00:07:16,362 --> 00:07:19,487
Two mafia guys are coming this way.

80
00:07:19,759 --> 00:07:20,563
The mafia?

81
00:07:20,563 --> 00:07:21,963
The mafia is coming here?

82
00:07:21,963 --> 00:07:23,349
Shut up, you!

83
00:07:23,575 --> 00:07:25,499
I think they're in the
same dodgy business as I am.

84
00:07:25,499 --> 00:07:27,333
You say so, but...

85
00:07:27,333 --> 00:07:29,416
You should go upstairs now.

86
00:07:30,122 --> 00:07:31,633
I've nothing to do with the mafia.

87
00:07:31,633 --> 00:07:32,713
Don't worry.

88
00:07:32,713 --> 00:07:35,505
We can't ignore someone
who is in trouble in a foreign country.

89
00:07:36,441 --> 00:07:37,608
This way.

90
00:07:38,209 --> 00:07:39,375
This way.

91
00:07:40,496 --> 00:07:42,579
This way. This way.

92
00:07:56,369 --> 00:08:00,683
Our group needs Lee, the big brother.

93
00:08:00,683 --> 00:08:03,558
"Our group"?
So, you're members of the mafia!

94
00:08:06,241 --> 00:08:07,949
We're not the mafia.

95
00:08:07,949 --> 00:08:10,806
We're his underlings.

96
00:08:10,806 --> 00:08:12,806
"Underlings." There you go!

97
00:08:12,806 --> 00:08:16,405
Huh? Underlings are hunting
their own big brother,

98
00:08:16,405 --> 00:08:18,264
it's such a moral degeneration
of chivalrous spirit.

99
00:08:18,264 --> 00:08:20,571
Hey, I don't want any trouble here.

100
00:08:20,571 --> 00:08:21,784
We need our big brother, Lee.

101
00:08:21,784 --> 00:08:23,588
We know he's here.

102
00:08:27,251 --> 00:08:31,251
They're not the mafia.

103
00:08:31,674 --> 00:08:33,270
They're my staff for the movie production.

104
00:08:41,065 --> 00:08:42,806
Sorry we made a fuss.

105
00:08:43,385 --> 00:08:44,148
Have some.

106
00:08:48,214 --> 00:08:51,964
Lee Punfa is a movie director.

107
00:08:52,674 --> 00:08:58,008
They're the producers who set up
the production company together.

108
00:08:58,629 --> 00:09:02,754
I guess they call it "a group" in China.
The same word we use for a yakuza group.

109
00:09:03,257 --> 00:09:05,674
Because he is Lee,
they call it the Lee group.

110
00:09:06,713 --> 00:09:08,472
It's so confusing.

111
00:09:09,257 --> 00:09:10,884
We found a new actor.

112
00:09:11,351 --> 00:09:13,311
He'd like to talk to you soon.

113
00:09:13,457 --> 00:09:14,066
Okay.

114
00:09:14,586 --> 00:09:15,806
I'll go back next week.

115
00:09:20,225 --> 00:09:23,854
The main actor of his new movie
has quit because of the pay,

116
00:09:23,854 --> 00:09:25,731
and the production has been stopped.

117
00:09:25,731 --> 00:09:31,317
Lee was fed up with the whole thing,
and he just left China. That's the story.

118
00:09:40,108 --> 00:09:40,941
I think I can...

119
00:09:54,646 --> 00:09:57,260
You can drink!

120
00:09:57,807 --> 00:10:01,687
His father, late Lee Guanrai,

121
00:10:01,687 --> 00:10:03,675
was a famous director of chivalry movies.

122
00:10:03,675 --> 00:10:05,509
What is a chivalry movie?

123
00:10:05,509 --> 00:10:10,287
Chivalry movies are
sword-fighting action films,

124
00:10:10,287 --> 00:10:12,293
which are based on
Chinese novels of the 1920s.

125
00:10:14,683 --> 00:10:16,804
Both you and your father are
film directors.

126
00:10:17,308 --> 00:10:22,921
I had aspirations to be a
film director like my father.

127
00:10:23,918 --> 00:10:26,335
I'm glad your new movie production
won't be canceled.

128
00:10:31,493 --> 00:10:35,826
We planned to remake the movie
which my father couldn't finish.

129
00:10:38,466 --> 00:10:42,376
When the main actor declined our offer,
I actually felt relieved.

130
00:10:44,708 --> 00:10:47,750
I have no confidence to remake it,
and I'm still scared.

131
00:10:48,913 --> 00:10:51,298
I'm scared of being
compared with him forever.

132
00:10:53,184 --> 00:10:54,730
You're different from your father!

133
00:10:55,069 --> 00:10:57,652
Please make your own movies!

134
00:10:57,937 --> 00:11:00,247
That's right. Just make movies!

135
00:11:00,247 --> 00:11:04,715
There are so many movie directors
who actually can't even make one.

136
00:11:06,641 --> 00:11:13,098
Actually, his movie's main actor
was a Japanese man.

137
00:11:15,132 --> 00:11:19,424
My father wished to see the guy again
after he had left China.

138
00:11:20,026 --> 00:11:22,950
I looked into his whereabouts,
but I couldn't find him.

139
00:11:23,981 --> 00:11:27,002
It was more than 40 years ago, right?

140
00:11:27,002 --> 00:11:29,793
It'd be difficult to find him.

141
00:11:31,013 --> 00:11:35,059
The movie you're gonna remake,
what's the story like?

142
00:11:37,736 --> 00:11:38,936
It's a long film.

143
00:11:38,936 --> 00:11:40,756
Can I explain it roughly?

144
00:11:41,456 --> 00:11:42,610
That's fine.

145
00:11:43,924 --> 00:11:45,083
Good evening.

146
00:11:45,429 --> 00:11:47,679
-You all are here.
-Welcome.

147
00:11:48,457 --> 00:11:51,208
Master, a beer and a
sweet rolled omelet, please.

148
00:11:51,208 --> 00:11:53,441
Miso soup with pork and veggies.
Large portion, please.

149
00:11:53,441 --> 00:11:54,123
Sure.

150
00:11:55,022 --> 00:11:59,470
Ms. Kosuzu, this is Lee Punfa.

151
00:11:59,794 --> 00:12:02,419
He is a film director.
Isn't he good-looking?

152
00:12:03,310 --> 00:12:05,776
I like sweet rolled omelets, too.

153
00:12:06,022 --> 00:12:08,022
Such a coincidence!

154
00:12:08,445 --> 00:12:10,126
His omelets are good, aren't they?

155
00:12:15,391 --> 00:12:16,811
It means "delicious."

156
00:12:20,945 --> 00:12:23,525
That... Great.

157
00:12:24,626 --> 00:12:27,334
Lee and Mr. Kanemoto, please continue.

158
00:12:27,925 --> 00:12:28,759
Shall we?

159
00:12:34,587 --> 00:12:36,869
It was in the 15th century,
during the Ming dynasty in China,

160
00:12:37,256 --> 00:12:43,477
a group of evil eunuchs
tried to take control of a region.

161
00:12:43,477 --> 00:12:47,766
They made the opposing minister
the scapegoat and executed him.

162
00:12:47,766 --> 00:12:51,813
Then they started hunting his family, too.

163
00:12:52,346 --> 00:12:57,385
The group discovered their whereabouts
and tried to kill all of them.

164
00:12:57,385 --> 00:13:00,078
They are now in an impending danger!

165
00:13:00,832 --> 00:13:04,980
They are forced into a corner.
Life is a candle flickering in the wind.

166
00:13:05,313 --> 00:13:08,966
Then, a martial artist and
a low-class eunuch in the evil group,

167
00:13:08,966 --> 00:13:12,616
a beautiful man called Xiao Ning
appears in front of the family.

168
00:13:12,616 --> 00:13:17,335
Xiao Ning was a subordinate
of the minister.

169
00:13:19,519 --> 00:13:21,726
Xiao Ning is a member of the evil group

170
00:13:21,726 --> 00:13:26,643
but has never forgotten
the minister's kindness.

171
00:13:28,136 --> 00:13:31,423
Xiao Ning, who decided to share his fate
with the minister's family,

172
00:13:32,104 --> 00:13:36,027
takes down the opponents with his swords.

173
00:13:40,544 --> 00:13:42,811
"I am who I am now.

174
00:13:46,443 --> 00:13:47,756
Every one of you..."

175
00:13:49,468 --> 00:13:52,764
Sorry for my betrayal!

176
00:13:52,850 --> 00:13:57,200
He said, "Sorry for my betrayal!"
What? Kosuzu, how did you...

177
00:14:17,825 --> 00:14:19,531
Xiao Ning!

178
00:14:36,841 --> 00:14:38,928
Did you perhaps...

179
00:14:42,307 --> 00:14:44,147
Father didn't cook very much.

180
00:14:46,954 --> 00:14:48,247
I know.

181
00:14:51,303 --> 00:14:55,619
You're the one who taught my father
how to cook rolled omelets?

182
00:15:00,101 --> 00:15:01,648
I thought so.

183
00:15:04,942 --> 00:15:05,942
Don't look at me.

184
00:15:24,217 --> 00:15:27,398
What's wrong with you?

185
00:15:28,578 --> 00:15:31,860
Is that person a man or a woman?

186
00:15:35,619 --> 00:15:37,619
I'd say both.

187
00:15:41,540 --> 00:15:43,426
Come inside for a cup of tea?

188
00:15:43,426 --> 00:15:45,176
I was just making one.

189
00:15:46,163 --> 00:15:46,995
Please.

190
00:15:47,361 --> 00:15:48,768
What can I say...

191
00:15:49,435 --> 00:15:51,315
How cruel the time is!

192
00:16:11,914 --> 00:16:12,956
Master.

193
00:16:16,460 --> 00:16:18,877
Can I come in?

194
00:16:20,008 --> 00:16:20,842
Sure.

195
00:16:33,357 --> 00:16:34,899
I met him...

196
00:16:36,404 --> 00:16:38,779
at a bar I used to work at.

197
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:45,470
Lee's father happened to be in Japan.

198
00:16:46,166 --> 00:16:51,833
He persuaded me to be the
main actor in his new movie.

199
00:16:53,750 --> 00:16:55,833
He was a gorgeous man,

200
00:16:56,458 --> 00:16:58,875
so I had a crush on him.

201
00:17:01,366 --> 00:17:03,199
He told me that he got divorced,

202
00:17:04,166 --> 00:17:09,041
and was living with a new-born baby son.

203
00:17:11,149 --> 00:17:12,857
So, I didn't think twice...

204
00:17:13,428 --> 00:17:15,582
and followed him to China.

205
00:17:19,779 --> 00:17:21,946
It looks great.

206
00:17:22,982 --> 00:17:25,357
Does Lee look like his father?

207
00:17:25,868 --> 00:17:27,327
Yes, he does.

208
00:17:28,708 --> 00:17:32,208
The moment he said "delicious"
in Chinese, I knew it.

209
00:17:33,375 --> 00:17:34,975
Can I have some, too?

210
00:17:35,458 --> 00:17:36,833
Of course you can.

211
00:17:37,586 --> 00:17:38,711
Please.

212
00:18:04,625 --> 00:18:05,916
The new movie...

213
00:18:06,856 --> 00:18:09,564
The production stopped
due to a shortage of money.

214
00:18:13,449 --> 00:18:15,115
After that,

215
00:18:15,982 --> 00:18:19,441
he suddenly lost his interest in me.

216
00:18:20,811 --> 00:18:24,393
I guess it wasn't a happy ending for me.

217
00:18:26,361 --> 00:18:27,270
Lee...

218
00:18:28,768 --> 00:18:30,743
said he was scared...

219
00:18:31,676 --> 00:18:35,025
of being compared with his father forever.

220
00:18:36,666 --> 00:18:38,333
He can't avoid that.

221
00:18:39,384 --> 00:18:42,782
The only thing he can do
is make movies. Silly boy.

222
00:18:45,447 --> 00:18:50,673
I believe you could tell him something.

223
00:18:56,257 --> 00:18:59,323
PRIVATELY RESERVED TODAY

224
00:18:59,323 --> 00:19:02,162
The night before Lee left Japan,

225
00:19:02,576 --> 00:19:06,249
all the regulars turned up
to say goodbye to him.

226
00:19:07,628 --> 00:19:08,641
Everyone.

227
00:19:09,238 --> 00:19:10,571
Cheers!

228
00:19:11,154 --> 00:19:13,529
Cheers!

229
00:19:19,051 --> 00:19:22,384
It was great to meet you all.

230
00:19:23,698 --> 00:19:26,808
Master, thank you so much for tonight.

231
00:19:26,808 --> 00:19:28,266
Okay. Here.

232
00:19:31,379 --> 00:19:35,921
Ms. Kosuzu, don't you cook
rolled omelets anymore?

233
00:19:36,902 --> 00:19:39,193
Master makes the best ones.

234
00:19:40,597 --> 00:19:44,774
Hey, I've got something to give you.

235
00:19:48,022 --> 00:19:49,438
Too beautiful!

236
00:19:49,921 --> 00:19:51,254
I can't believe it!

237
00:19:51,254 --> 00:19:52,367
It can't be true!

238
00:19:52,367 --> 00:19:53,909
Is this really you?

239
00:20:09,341 --> 00:20:13,674
Your father loved only you and movies.

240
00:20:14,458 --> 00:20:15,666
Keep up the good work.

241
00:20:20,347 --> 00:20:21,181
Yes.

242
00:20:22,385 --> 00:20:24,992
Shall we also have rolled omelets today?

243
00:20:27,028 --> 00:20:29,694
To celebrate Lee's new start,
I'll treat you all.

244
00:20:30,892 --> 00:20:32,976
Great!

245
00:20:33,825 --> 00:20:36,325
-Does he really?
-That's unusual.

246
00:20:39,869 --> 00:20:42,327
Three months have passed since then.

247
00:21:06,926 --> 00:21:07,846
Surrender!

248
00:21:21,148 --> 00:21:22,282
You...

249
00:21:41,668 --> 00:21:44,834
Sorry for my betrayal!

250
00:21:44,834 --> 00:21:46,607
-Cut!
-Cut!

251
00:21:48,137 --> 00:21:49,090
Getting better.

252
00:21:49,090 --> 00:21:49,837
But,

253
00:21:49,837 --> 00:21:52,519
a bit cooler look on your face.

254
00:21:52,519 --> 00:21:53,765
You look so rigid.

255
00:21:54,211 --> 00:21:55,984
Try to relax.

256
00:21:56,444 --> 00:21:57,731
Let's have a break.

257
00:22:09,107 --> 00:22:10,953
Eunuchs...

258
00:22:11,833 --> 00:22:14,038
In exchange for their career,

259
00:22:15,105 --> 00:22:18,084
they had to give up
their masculine function.

260
00:22:19,788 --> 00:22:22,628
They're unfortunate and sad creatures.

261
00:22:27,467 --> 00:22:32,132
If you don't get that properly,

262
00:22:33,434 --> 00:22:35,428
your acting gets very shallow.

263
00:22:35,428 --> 00:22:36,228
Hey, you!

264
00:22:36,766 --> 00:22:38,272
That's not the right costume.

265
00:22:38,272 --> 00:22:40,179
Change it quick.

266
00:22:40,519 --> 00:22:42,106
Hurry up, or you'll be fired.

267
00:22:42,726 --> 00:22:43,566
You got it.

268
00:22:43,860 --> 00:22:45,073
